JV Football @ Leyton (Dalton)
Monday, Sept. 14th @ 5pm

Leyton Activity Contest COVID-19 Procedures

Spectators
🏈 50% capacity indoors, 75% capacity outdoors
🏈 Families should sit together in groups of less than 8 people, 6 feet apart
🏈 Visitors will be directed to North end, Home will occupy South end of gym
🏈 Visitors will be directed to the East side, Home will occupy the West side of the football field
🏈 Masks encouraged when social distancing is not occurring
🏈 Spectators should leave the facility immediately after the conclusion of the game. There shall be no
congregating or socializing in the building or on field
🏈 All K-8 students must be accompanied by their parents/guardians

Concession Stand
🏈 Separate Lines for home/visitors, 6 feet apart, indicated by roped off areas
🏈 Tables arranged to encourage social distancing
🏈 Concession stand workers will wear masks and gloves

Participants/officials/ workers
🏈 Masks encouraged when not competing
🏈 Visiting teams will health check all personnel and validate that all have been checked
🏈 Sanitation station available

Sept. 12, 2020

Teams:Bridgeport, Mitchell, Potter-Dix, Hyannis

Time:9:00 AM

Locker Rooms:Teams will be assigned dressing rooms upon arrival.

Admission:$5.00-Adults $4.00-Students

Schedule: Game 1 will begin at 9:00 and the following games will begin after both teams have had the prescribed warm-up time.

Game Venue
Game 1 Bridgeport vs. Hyannis New Gym

Effective immediately NSAA member schools may hold open gyms for basketball, football, soccer, and wrestling with the following restrictions:

Individual skills and workouts only

No physical contact with others

No sharing of equipment

No grouping of students

Open gym supervisors are required to enforce the above restrictions.

Prioritizing the health and safety of all students and staff must remain the focus of each NSAA member school.

post_text:
A message from Mr. Patrick

Potter-Dix Public Schools will be closed the week of March 16-21, including Prom scheduled for March 21st.

The critical consideration in this decision is the fact that many students, staff, and families were traveling during spring break. This decision allows everyone an extra week to follow the health department’s recommendations of social distancing while self monitoring for symptoms as they return from traveling.

I know that any decision I make greatly impacts students, staff, families and our communities. This is a decision I do not take lightly and want to look out for the health of our students, staff, and communities.

At this time, I plan on having school in session Monday March 23rd.
